residuals <- data.notrend - fitted(seas.6)

plot(TIME, residuals, type = "l")

acf(residuals)

pacf(residuals)

n <- length(residuals)

norder <- 5

p <- 1:norder - 1
q <- 1:norder - 1

aic <- matrix(0, nrow = norder, ncol = norder)

for (i in 1:norder) {
  for (j in 1: norder) {
    modij <- arima(residuals, order = c(p[i],0,q[j]), method='ML')
    aic[i,j] <- modij$aic-2*(p[i]+q[j]+1)+2*(p[i]+q[j]+1)*n/(n-p[i]-q[j]-2)
  }
}

# Function to perform Augmented Dickey-Fuller test manually
adf_test <- function(x, lag.max = NULL) {
  if (is.null(lag.max)) {
    lag.max <- floor(12*(length(x)/100)^0.25)
  }
  
  p_values <- numeric(lag.max)
  for (k in 1:lag.max) {
    reg <- lm(diff(x) ~ lag(diff(x), k = k))
    p_values[k] <- summary(reg)$coefficients[2, "Pr(>|t|)"]
  }
  
  adf_stat <- min(abs(qnorm(p_values)))
  p_value <- 1 - pnorm(adf_stat)
  
  cat("Augmented Dickey-Fuller Test\n")
  cat("ADF Statistic:", adf_stat, "\n")
  cat("p-value:", p_value, "\n")
  
  if (p_value < 0.05) {
    cat("Reject null hypothesis: The series is stationary\n")
  } else {
    cat("Fail to reject null hypothesis: The series is not stationary\n")
  }
  
  return(list(statistic = adf_stat, p.value = p_value))
}

# Perform Augmented Dickey-Fuller test on residuals
adf_test_res <- adf_test(residuals)

# Check for homoscedasticity (Breusch-Pagan test)
# Calculate residuals
residuals <- data.notrend - fitted(seas.6)

# Fit a linear model to test for homoscedasticity
model <- lm(residuals^2 ~ fitted(seas.6))

# Extract residuals from the model
model_residuals <- residuals(model)

# Perform Breusch-Pagan test manually
n <- length(model_residuals)
x <- seq_len(n)

# Fit a linear model to the squared residuals
lm_squared_residuals <- lm(model_residuals^2 ~ x)

# Obtain the test statistic
bp_test_statistic <- summary(lm_squared_residuals)$fstatistic[1]

# Calculate the p-value
bp_test_p_value <- pf(bp_test_statistic, 1, n - 2, lower.tail = FALSE)

# Print the test results
cat("Breusch-Pagan Test Results:\n")
## Breusch-Pagan Test Results:
cat("Test Statistic:", bp_test_statistic, "\n")
## Test Statistic: 7.01017
cat("p-value:", bp_test_p_value, "\n")
## p-value: 0.008430149
